added.title: Love Monsters
added.description: Despite Raven's warnings, Starfire showers love on the adorable twin destroyers of the universe.

added.title: Matched
added.description: When a computer dating program matches Beast Boy to Raven, he tries wooing her to disastrous effect.

added.title: No Power
added.description: Robin challenges the gang not to use their powers and they're more successful than he suspects!

added.title: Caged Tiger
added.description: When Robin, Cyborg, and Beast Boy get trapped in an elevator the limits of their friendship are tested, while Starfire and Raven bond with a supervillain.

added.description: Starfire convinces the reluctant Titans to try defeating their enemies with compassion rather than violence.

added.title: Opposites
added.description: Cyborg has a star-crossed crush on Jinx, the cutest member of The Hive.

added.title: Be Mine
added.description: Beast Boy invites Tara to the Titan's Valentine's Day dance and she accepts in order to destroy all of the Titans and exact revenge on Beast Boy.

added.title: Terra-ized
added.description: Beast Boy falls for Terra despite clear signs that she is more interested in destroying the Titans.

added.title: Second Christmas
added.description: The Titans trick Starfire into believing in second Christmas with second Santa.

added.title: Waffles
added.description: Cyborg and Beast Boy annoy the other Titans by refusing to say anything but "Waffles."

added.title: The Heart
added.description: When Mr. Robinson accidentally let slip how little he cares for Gumball and Darwin, they react by giving him the cold shoulder.  Surprisingly Mr. Robinson misses them and tries to win back their friendship. After a few failed attempts, Gumball and Darwin realize that Mr. Robinson's heart is protecting him, so they give it an intense affection overload.

added.title: The Matchmaker
added.description: Gumball catches Darwin gazing wistfully at a photo of Teri on Elmore Plus and secretly enlists Carrie to help bring them together. But when they can't make Darwin and Teri's love blossom naturally, they decide to make it happen supernaturally.

added.title: The Romantic
added.description: After Gumball convinces himself that Penny doesn't love him as much as she used to, he decides to put together a romantic quest to remind her of all the good times they've had together. But Gumball's romantic gesture backfires, landing Penny and maybe their relationship in serious peril.

added.title: The Love
added.description: The residents of Elmore search for the meaning of love.

added.title: The Promise
added.description: Darwin has promised to play video games with Gumball, but there is a Banana Joe-shaped problem...

added.title: The Castle
added.description: When Mom is away "anything goes" and Dad's lack of rules soon attracts unwelcome houseguests.

added.title: The Boombox
added.description: Gumball and Darwin try to understand Juke's urgent Beatbox message, but why won't he just speak English?!!

added.title: The Tape
added.description: Gumball and Darwin fail to make some instant homemade movie classics.

added.title: The Finale
added.description: The Wattersons are surprised to discover that their past actions have consequences.

added.title: The Kiss
added.description: Gumball is traumatised when accidentally kissed on the mouth by his Grandma JoJo.

added.title: The Internet
added.description: Gumball accidentally uploads a video of himself, and then demands The Internet take it down...personally!

added.title: The World
added.description: The amazing world of Elmore is full of inanimate objects that aren't nearly as inanimate as you might hope!

added.description: The Trio finds gold in the muddy depths of the Creek so Craig builds a rig to recover it.

added.description: When a kid claims dibs on the Stump, Craig has no choice but to take them to court. Dibs Court.

added.description: Panda volunteers to be Lucy's partner for a dance contest. But Panda doesn't have the heart to tell Lucy that she's a terrible dancer.

added.description: To recover a missing package, the Bears get help from Ranger Tabes, an eccentric forest ranger. But her overblown sense of justice might be too much for the Bears to handle.

added.description: The Bears switch bedrooms for the night and get a glimpse of the living space of one of their brothers. But the deeper they go, hidden secrets are revealed.

added.description: Feeling unappreciated, Ice Bear leaves his brothers to be the chef of a restaurant. Desperate to fill the void, Grizz and Panda look for Ice Bear's replacement.

added.description: Steven goes to the lighthouse to watch scary movies with Ronaldo, Lars and Sadie.

added.description: Steven has to get Connie home before it snows.

added.title: Marble Madness
added.description: Steven and the Gems encounter another droid from space.

added.description: Steven heads to the woods to train with a powerful mentor.

added.description: Steven heads to the Diamonds for advice on how to control his new powers.

added.title: Everything's Fine

added.title: I Am My Monster

added.title: The Future
added.description: Steven is finally ready to move on.

added.description: Finn and Jake volunteer for a dangerous assignment: currying rare tarts for a meeting of Ooo royalty.

added.title: The Pods
added.description: Finn and Jake must sort out the good magic beans from the bad.

added.description: Finn needs to find a princess willing to give up a lock of her hair to save Jake from a balding witch.

added.description: Finn and Jake get to live like royalty, but soon fine the easy life doesn't suit them. Or at least not Finn.

added.description: The guys have to get Muscle Man married.

added.description: Mordecai and CJ want to go on a romantic date.

added.description: Mordecai tries to prove to Margaret that camping is cool.

added.description: Mordecai needs access to the computer so he and Rigby challenge Muscle Man and High Five Ghost to a basketball game for a week's worth of computer time.

added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want cool bikes because if their bikes are cool, then they are cool.

added.description: Mordecai and Rigby are sick of Benson's house rules and want to live without them.

added.description: Mordecai and Rigby don't want Pops to be called a loser so they say that they'll join him in a rap battle.

added.description: Mordecai and Rigby make a bet with Margaret and Eileen that they can get a girl's phone number by cruising.

added.description: Mordecai and Rigby need to get rid of graffiti in the park.

added.title: Weekend at Benson's
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby accidentally knock out Benson and try to cover it up.

added.title: Fortune Cookie
added.description: Rigby swaps fortune cookie fortunes with Benson.

added.title: Think Positive
added.description: Pops orders Benson to stop yelling at Mordecai and Rigby.

added.description: Muscle Man has to impress his girlfriend's parents at a fancy dinner.

added.description: The girls are so busy fighting crime that the Professor doesn't get to see them anymore. So he creates a superhero suit for himself. Unfortunately, he starts cramping their superhero style.

added.description: Another one of the Professor's plans goes awry when he tries to switch apples for oranges causing the entire town to switch from one body to another. The girls must remedy the situation.

added.description: Town and Out: When the Professor gets a new job, the girls have to move away from Townsville. They try to make the best of it but it's just not the same. In fact, it's downright awful./Child Fearing: When the Mayor needs someone to babysit the girls for him, Mojo is unwittingly drafted. Little does Mojo know, taking care of three little girls can be a big hassle.

added.title: Jewel of the Aisle/Super Zeroes
added.description: Jewel of the Isle: A crook hides a huge diamond in a box of the girls' favorite cereal. But how can he trick the girls into giving him some cereal in order to get the jewel back?/Super Zeroes: The girls don't think they have enough superhero accessories like those found in the comic books. They begin to emulate their favorite characters, complete with gadgets and gizmos.

added.title: Bubblevision/Bought and Scold
added.description: Bubblevision: Bubbles' fighting has been really terribly lately and the Professor discovers she needs glasses. Bubbles is humiliated by these huge, horrible things and never wants to see or be seen again./Bough and Scold: When Princess buys Townsville, she makes crime legal. Now, the girls have nothing to do and the town is in shambles.

added.title: Hot Air Buffoon/Ploys R' Us
added.description: Hot Air Buffoon: The Mayor realizes the girls are doing all the work in his city for him. So he mans a hot air balloon and starts fighting crime the old-fashioned way./Ploys R' Us: The girls wake up to find their room filled with toys. They soon figure out that the Professor has been sleepwalking and stealing. Instead of reporting it, the girls take advantage of the situation.

added.title: Gettin' Twiggy with It/Cop Out

But when Mitch flushes Twiggy down the toilet, he emerges bigger and badder than ever./Cop Out: A lazy Townsville cop gets fired and blames the girls for saving the day too often, thereby stealing his job. Now, it's payback time and he has the perfect plan to stop those pint-size punks.
